Sure! Here are some of the best colleges in the USA that provide professional training in Hip-Hop Dance:

1. Broadway Dance Center - Located in New York City, Broadway Dance Center offers a wide range of dance classes, including Hip-Hop. They have renowned faculty members and provide professional training for aspiring dancers. [Visit Website](https://www.broadwaydancecenter.com/){:target="_blank"}

2. The Ailey School - Based in New York City, The Ailey School is affiliated with the Alvin Ailey American Dance Theater. They offer a diverse curriculum that includes Hip-Hop dance training. [Visit Website](https://www.alvinailey.org/school){:target="_blank"}

3. University of Southern California (USC) Glorya Kaufman School of Dance - Located in Los Angeles, USC offers a Bachelor of Fine Arts (BFA) in Dance with a focus on various dance styles, including Hip-Hop. The program provides comprehensive training and performance opportunities. [Visit Website](https://kaufman.usc.edu/){:target="_blank"}

4. The Juilliard School - Situated in New York City, Juilliard is renowned for its performing arts programs. They offer a Bachelor of Fine Arts (BFA) in Dance, which includes training in various dance styles, including Hip-Hop. [Visit Website](https://www.juilliard.edu/dance){:target="_blank"}

5. University of the Arts - Located in Philadelphia, the University of the Arts offers a Bachelor of Fine Arts (BFA) in Dance with a focus on contemporary dance forms, including Hip-Hop. The program emphasizes technical training and artistic development. [Visit Website](https://www.uarts.edu/academics/dance){:target="_blank"}

6. California Institute of the Arts (CalArts) - Situated in Valencia, California, CalArts offers a Bachelor of Fine Arts (BFA) in Dance with a diverse curriculum that includes Hip-Hop dance training. The program focuses on developing versatile and innovative dancers. [Visit Website](https://dance.calarts.edu/){:target="_blank"}

7. University of North Carolina School of the Arts (UNCSA) - Located in Winston-Salem, North Carolina, UNCSA offers a Bachelor of Fine Arts (BFA) in Dance with a concentration in Contemporary Dance. The program includes training in various dance styles, including Hip-Hop. [Visit Website](https://www.uncsa.edu/dance/index.aspx){:target="_blank"}

Please note that these are just a few examples, and there are many other colleges and universities in the USA that offer professional training in Hip-Hop Dance. It's always recommended to research and visit the websites of each institution to gather more information about their specific programs and admission requirements.
